WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
If you've got a Bible with you,

2
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:02.760
do please turn with me once again

3
00:00:02.760 --> 00:00:04.500
to Ephesians chapter one.

4
00:00:05.400 --> 00:00:06.840
Ephesians chapter one.

5
00:00:10.680 --> 00:00:11.840
As you're turning there,

6
00:00:11.840 --> 00:00:14.640
we've seen already that the Apostle Paul's ministry

7
00:00:14.640 --> 00:00:19.640
was marked by praise and prayer really.

8
00:00:19.680 --> 00:00:22.360
You see that in Ephesians here at the start.

9
00:00:22.360 --> 00:00:24.080
He's beginning with this prayer of praise

10
00:00:24.080 --> 00:00:26.320
that we've been looking at over the past couple of weeks.

11
00:00:26.320 --> 00:00:29.200
He's praising God for every spiritual blessing

12
00:00:29.200 --> 00:00:31.440
that is ours in Christ.

13
00:00:31.440 --> 00:00:35.120
And he now moves from praise to a prayer of intercession.

14
00:00:35.120 --> 00:00:37.240
He's praying for the Ephesians,

15
00:00:37.240 --> 00:00:39.120
and those who will receive this letter.

16
00:00:39.120 --> 00:00:41.640
And he lets them know that he's praying for them.

17
00:00:41.640 --> 00:00:42.960
And he doesn't just let them know that

18
00:00:42.960 --> 00:00:43.800
he's praying for them,

19
00:00:43.800 --> 00:00:48.800
he lets them know what he is praying for them as well.

20
00:00:48.800 --> 00:00:50.080
And so that's what we're reading about.

21
00:00:50.080 --> 00:00:52.520
His prayer for them as we come to Ephesians

22
00:00:52.520 --> 00:00:57.520
chapter one verses 15 down to the end of verse 23.

23
00:01:00.200 --> 00:01:01.240
It says, for this reason,

24
00:01:01.240 --> 00:01:05.480
because I have heard of your faith in the Lord Jesus

25
00:01:05.480 --> 00:01:08.280
and your love toward all the saints,

26
00:01:08.280 --> 00:01:10.600
I do not cease to give thanks for you,

27
00:01:10.600 --> 00:01:13.000
remembering you in my prayers,

28
00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:15.400
that the God of our Lord Jesus Christ,

29
00:01:15.400 --> 00:01:17.100
the Father of glory,

30
00:01:17.100 --> 00:01:19.300
may give you the spirit of wisdom

31
00:01:19.300 --> 00:01:22.240
and of revelation in the knowledge of him.

32
00:01:22.240 --> 00:01:24.920
Having the eyes of your hearts enlightened

33
00:01:24.920 --> 00:01:26.560
that you may know what is the hope

34
00:01:26.560 --> 00:01:28.480
to which he has called you.

35
00:01:28.480 --> 00:01:32.320
What are the riches of his glorious inheritance in the saints?

36
00:01:32.320 --> 00:01:34.120
And what is the immeasurable greatness

37
00:01:34.120 --> 00:01:36.900
of his power toward us who believe?

38
00:01:36.900 --> 00:01:39.560
According to the working of his great might

39
00:01:39.560 --> 00:01:42.260
that he worked in Christ when he raised him from the dead

40
00:01:42.260 --> 00:01:45.640
and seated him at the right hand in the heavenly places,

41
00:01:45.640 --> 00:01:50.360
far above all rule and authority and power and dominion

42
00:01:50.360 --> 00:01:52.680
and above every name that is named.

43
00:01:52.680 --> 00:01:56.560
Not only in this age, but also in the one to come.

44
00:01:56.560 --> 00:01:58.800
And he put all things under his feet

45
00:01:58.800 --> 00:02:02.680
and gave him as head over all things to the church,

46
00:02:02.680 --> 00:02:07.680
which is his body, the fullness of him who fills all in all.

47
00:02:07.920 --> 00:02:09.320
This is the word of the Lord.

48
00:02:11.280 --> 00:02:12.720
Let's pray once again.

49
00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:15.640
Lord, as we come now to your word,

50
00:02:15.640 --> 00:02:18.520
I pray that you would by your spirit open our eyes

51
00:02:18.520 --> 00:02:20.800
that we may see wondrous things here.

52
00:02:21.720 --> 00:02:23.240
Would I pray that you would fill us

53
00:02:23.280 --> 00:02:28.280
with a desire to know them and the faith to believe in them?

54
00:02:28.720 --> 00:02:30.840
Lord, I pray that as we see them

55
00:02:30.840 --> 00:02:33.200
that you would change us through them.

56
00:02:33.200 --> 00:02:35.600
Would open our eyes to see more of you we pray

57
00:02:35.600 --> 00:02:37.400
in Jesus' name, amen.

58
00:02:39.080 --> 00:02:42.960
Just over 18 years ago now,

59
00:02:42.960 --> 00:02:46.160
I went to England for the very first time.

60
00:02:46.160 --> 00:02:47.360
And when I was there,

61
00:02:47.360 --> 00:02:51.480
I met the most beautiful girl I'd ever seen

62
00:02:51.480 --> 00:02:52.800
in Stoke-on-Trents.

63
00:02:52.800 --> 00:02:54.680
I remember the day vividly.

64
00:02:54.680 --> 00:02:56.800
I walked into the city center.

65
00:02:56.800 --> 00:02:59.800
We were going to this event and there was Julia.

66
00:02:59.800 --> 00:03:03.360
She was blonde hair and white top and yellow skirt.

67
00:03:03.360 --> 00:03:07.040
And she has very little recollection of the day at all.

68
00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:09.780
But I remember her stood there and I met her.

69
00:03:10.760 --> 00:03:14.440
And so that was day one of when we met.

70
00:03:14.440 --> 00:03:15.360
And then a few weeks ago,

71
00:03:15.360 --> 00:03:17.240
we were kind of giving this little exercise

72
00:03:17.240 --> 00:03:18.200
to work through together.

73
00:03:18.200 --> 00:03:19.640
And the exercise was this,

74
00:03:19.640 --> 00:03:21.280
go away for 10 or 15 minutes

75
00:03:21.280 --> 00:03:26.120
and find out something that you do not know about your spouse.

76
00:03:26.120 --> 00:03:28.840
And at the start, it was kind of hard to like,

77
00:03:28.840 --> 00:03:30.520
okay, what do we actually not know?

78
00:03:30.520 --> 00:03:32.080
But after you start thinking and talking,

79
00:03:32.080 --> 00:03:34.320
you realize that even now,

80
00:03:34.320 --> 00:03:38.200
there are still things about each other to discover.

81
00:03:38.200 --> 00:03:40.600
Well, the focal point of what Paul is praying here

82
00:03:40.600 --> 00:03:44.480
is that the Ephesians might know him.

83
00:03:44.480 --> 00:03:46.880
It's the knowledge of him he's praying about

84
00:03:46.880 --> 00:03:48.800
at the end of verse 17.

85
00:03:48.840 --> 00:03:51.560
The reason why I mentioned Julia and getting to know her

86
00:03:51.560 --> 00:03:54.080
is to point out a couple of things about the knowledge

87
00:03:54.080 --> 00:03:57.720
that Paul speaks about at the end of verse 17

88
00:03:57.720 --> 00:04:00.400
where he talks about the knowledge of him.

89
00:04:00.400 --> 00:04:02.480
First of all, the knowledge is personal.

90
00:04:02.480 --> 00:04:04.520
So it's not so much about knowing something

91
00:04:04.520 --> 00:04:05.760
as it is someone.

92
00:04:05.760 --> 00:04:06.600
So it's not like, I don't know,

93
00:04:06.600 --> 00:04:08.440
reading a Wikipedia entry.

94
00:04:09.840 --> 00:04:12.360
You know, it's getting to know somebody.

95
00:04:13.360 --> 00:04:14.960
So I think about like when Julia and I

96
00:04:14.960 --> 00:04:16.560
were first in contact with each other,

97
00:04:16.560 --> 00:04:17.760
we were in different parts of the world.

98
00:04:17.800 --> 00:04:19.880
So there were a lot of emails exchanged.

99
00:04:19.880 --> 00:04:21.520
Let me tell you, I didn't read those emails

100
00:04:21.520 --> 00:04:23.240
like a Wikipedia entry.

101
00:04:23.240 --> 00:04:25.800
You know, there was a personal dynamic to it.

102
00:04:25.800 --> 00:04:26.960
That was different.

103
00:04:28.080 --> 00:04:29.800
And it's interesting, when you look at knowledge

104
00:04:29.800 --> 00:04:31.760
across Scripture, this word knowing,

105
00:04:31.760 --> 00:04:34.080
it is actually a word that is used to refer

106
00:04:34.080 --> 00:04:37.200
to the relationship of a husband and a wife.

107
00:04:37.200 --> 00:04:39.280
It is an intimate knowledge that is here.

108
00:04:39.280 --> 00:04:42.680
So it's personal, but it's also progressive.

109
00:04:42.680 --> 00:04:45.560
So you can know and love someone for years

110
00:04:45.560 --> 00:04:49.120
and still have more to discover about them.

111
00:04:49.120 --> 00:04:50.640
So here Paul is writing to people

112
00:04:50.640 --> 00:04:52.800
who have already come to know the Lord

113
00:04:52.800 --> 00:04:56.200
and yet he's praying that they might know him.

114
00:04:56.200 --> 00:04:59.200
In other words, he's praying that they might know him more.

115
00:04:59.200 --> 00:05:01.440
So whether you've known him for five minutes

116
00:05:01.440 --> 00:05:05.400
or for 50 years, you're still just scratching

117
00:05:05.400 --> 00:05:06.480
at the surface.

118
00:05:06.480 --> 00:05:09.400
There's more to know when you know the Lord.

119
00:05:10.560 --> 00:05:12.120
So it's personal and progressive.

120
00:05:13.080 --> 00:05:16.000
So this is the main point of Paul's letter, rather,

121
00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:19.880
that Christians might come to know God better.

122
00:05:19.880 --> 00:05:23.560
This is what he is praying here for them.

123
00:05:23.560 --> 00:05:25.240
So as we get started looking at this together,

124
00:05:25.240 --> 00:05:26.560
just a couple of personal questions.

125
00:05:26.560 --> 00:05:29.480
One is, do you know God?

126
00:05:29.480 --> 00:05:31.680
Not just do you know things about God?

127
00:05:31.680 --> 00:05:34.520
Do you know the Lord personally?

128
00:05:35.480 --> 00:05:38.360
The second question is, are you growing

129
00:05:38.360 --> 00:05:39.840
in your knowledge of him?

130
00:05:39.840 --> 00:05:41.800
Do you want to know him more?

131
00:05:41.800 --> 00:05:45.560
Can you see that you're growing in your knowledge of him?

132
00:05:46.480 --> 00:05:48.760
Well, what Paul is praying here, what he writes here,

133
00:05:48.760 --> 00:05:49.760
helps us with this.

134
00:05:49.760 --> 00:05:51.320
And so we're gonna look at what he prays

135
00:05:51.320 --> 00:05:53.760
by dividing it up into three questions.

136
00:05:53.760 --> 00:05:55.080
There's three questions you came,

137
00:05:55.080 --> 00:05:57.320
not knowing you were gonna ask me this morning.

138
00:05:57.320 --> 00:05:58.840
But these are the questions you're gonna ask.

139
00:05:58.840 --> 00:06:01.560
We're gonna ask this of the text really together.

140
00:06:01.560 --> 00:06:02.760
And here's the three questions.

141
00:06:02.760 --> 00:06:03.800
I'll go ahead and tell you what they are.

142
00:06:03.800 --> 00:06:06.840
One is, how can we know that we know God?

143
00:06:07.720 --> 00:06:10.400
The second question is, how can we grow

144
00:06:10.400 --> 00:06:12.520
in the knowledge of God?

145
00:06:12.520 --> 00:06:14.400
And the third question we're gonna ask is,

146
00:06:14.400 --> 00:06:16.960
well, what are some examples of what that looks like?

147
00:06:16.960 --> 00:06:18.920
Okay, so what are some examples?

148
00:06:18.920 --> 00:06:22.800
So first of all, how can we know that we know God?

149
00:06:22.800 --> 00:06:24.800
Well, verse 15, right at the start

150
00:06:24.800 --> 00:06:26.640
of Paul telling them he's praying,

151
00:06:26.640 --> 00:06:29.080
he tells them that he is certain

152
00:06:29.080 --> 00:06:32.520
that they are essentially real Christians.

153
00:06:32.520 --> 00:06:35.080
He knows that they are true believers.

154
00:06:35.120 --> 00:06:36.920
He's not met all of them personally,

155
00:06:36.920 --> 00:06:38.680
but from what he has heard about them,

156
00:06:38.680 --> 00:06:42.160
he has been convinced that they really know the Lord.

157
00:06:42.160 --> 00:06:45.160
And so this is the reason why he is praying for them,

158
00:06:45.160 --> 00:06:46.600
he writes.

159
00:06:46.600 --> 00:06:50.960
So what convinces him that they truly know the Lord?

160
00:06:50.960 --> 00:06:53.040
What is the evidence that demonstrates

161
00:06:53.040 --> 00:06:55.440
somebody really knows God?

162
00:06:57.040 --> 00:06:58.440
What would be the evidence that would come through

163
00:06:58.440 --> 00:06:59.280
in our lives?

164
00:06:59.280 --> 00:07:00.560
What's two things?

165
00:07:00.560 --> 00:07:03.960
One is faith, and the other is love.

166
00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:05.520
So you got faith and love here together.

167
00:07:05.520 --> 00:07:08.840
So you got a vertical one, faith in the Lord Jesus Christ.

168
00:07:08.840 --> 00:07:10.200
He says, I've heard about that.

169
00:07:10.200 --> 00:07:11.520
And the other is horizontal,

170
00:07:11.520 --> 00:07:13.200
and your love for all the saints.

171
00:07:13.200 --> 00:07:15.200
And both are crucially important

172
00:07:15.200 --> 00:07:18.920
when it comes to knowing whether or not you know the Lord.

173
00:07:18.920 --> 00:07:20.760
So let's just take him one at a time.

174
00:07:20.760 --> 00:07:25.680
He's heard about their faith in the Lord Jesus.

175
00:07:25.680 --> 00:07:28.200
So if you were to ask Paul a question like this,

176
00:07:28.200 --> 00:07:32.640
what must someone believe in order to be saved?

177
00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:35.400
His answer would be simple.

178
00:07:35.400 --> 00:07:39.120
Well, they must believe on the Lord Jesus Christ.

179
00:07:39.120 --> 00:07:40.360
You see that here in the text,

180
00:07:40.360 --> 00:07:41.480
but you also see it in other places.

181
00:07:41.480 --> 00:07:43.880
You go back to Acts chapter 16,

182
00:07:43.880 --> 00:07:47.160
and you've got the interaction with the Philippian jailer.

183
00:07:47.160 --> 00:07:50.120
And the jailer asked Paul and Silas,

184
00:07:50.120 --> 00:07:52.480
sirs, what must I do to be saved?

185
00:07:52.480 --> 00:07:54.760
Acts 16, 31, the answer comes back.

186
00:07:54.760 --> 00:07:57.080
Believe on the Lord Jesus Christ,

187
00:07:57.080 --> 00:07:58.800
and you will be saved.

188
00:07:58.800 --> 00:08:02.000
And he goes on to explain further about who Jesus is.

189
00:08:02.000 --> 00:08:04.640
But note the simplicity of that.

190
00:08:04.640 --> 00:08:07.480
Believe on Jesus, and you'll be saved.

191
00:08:08.360 --> 00:08:11.120
Well, we might say, well, there is a lot more to this

192
00:08:11.120 --> 00:08:12.320
than just that.

193
00:08:13.520 --> 00:08:15.160
I mean, think about all the doctrines

194
00:08:15.160 --> 00:08:16.800
we need to cover with people.

195
00:08:16.800 --> 00:08:18.840
Like there's like the inspiration of Scripture,

196
00:08:18.840 --> 00:08:20.560
and we could go on and on listing

197
00:08:20.560 --> 00:08:22.080
all of these important doctrines,

198
00:08:22.080 --> 00:08:24.440
and they all are all important.

199
00:08:25.840 --> 00:08:27.720
Every doctrine is important

200
00:08:27.720 --> 00:08:29.440
if it's coming from Scripture.

201
00:08:30.440 --> 00:08:33.480
And the fact is, as people grow in Christ,

202
00:08:33.480 --> 00:08:37.280
they will believe what Scripture says about Him

203
00:08:37.280 --> 00:08:38.320
in more depth.

204
00:08:38.320 --> 00:08:40.720
But we think of a new believer,

205
00:08:40.720 --> 00:08:42.920
like a baby doesn't know much

206
00:08:42.920 --> 00:08:45.680
and can't articulate much about his mother,

207
00:08:45.680 --> 00:08:48.800
but the baby knows who his mother is.

208
00:08:48.800 --> 00:08:50.240
There is a relationship there,

209
00:08:50.240 --> 00:08:52.040
and as the child grows,

210
00:08:52.040 --> 00:08:55.480
their knowledge grows as well.

211
00:08:55.480 --> 00:08:58.880
So everything begins with our faith in Jesus Christ.

212
00:08:58.920 --> 00:09:00.600
We're saved through faith in Him

213
00:09:00.600 --> 00:09:02.600
by trusting in Jesus and Him alone

214
00:09:02.600 --> 00:09:04.840
as our Savior and as our King.

215
00:09:04.840 --> 00:09:07.080
And as we grow, we learn more,

216
00:09:07.080 --> 00:09:12.080
but we continue to trust in Him and in Him alone.

217
00:09:13.320 --> 00:09:15.240
So the answer to whether or not you know God

218
00:09:15.240 --> 00:09:17.320
is found in what you're putting your trust in,

219
00:09:17.320 --> 00:09:20.160
or are you putting your trust in Jesus?

220
00:09:20.160 --> 00:09:22.560
Not in your works, not in some system,

221
00:09:22.560 --> 00:09:25.200
not in how much you know or how much you do,

222
00:09:25.200 --> 00:09:28.320
is your trust in Jesus and Him alone to save you.

223
00:09:29.320 --> 00:09:31.360
And there's another piece of evidence here

224
00:09:31.360 --> 00:09:34.400
that demonstrates someone that someone truly knows the Lord,

225
00:09:34.400 --> 00:09:37.520
and that is love for all the saints.

226
00:09:37.520 --> 00:09:39.440
He says, I've heard about your faith in the Lord Jesus

227
00:09:39.440 --> 00:09:41.920
and your love towards all the saints.

228
00:09:41.920 --> 00:09:44.000
So one of the ways you can see

229
00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:48.200
that someone knows the Lord is in their love for others,

230
00:09:48.200 --> 00:09:51.200
particularly their brothers and sisters in Christ.

231
00:09:51.200 --> 00:09:53.600
Just be clear, it isn't our love for God

232
00:09:53.600 --> 00:09:58.320
or for others that saves us, it is His love for us.

233
00:09:58.360 --> 00:10:01.360
But when you come to know His love in Jesus,

234
00:10:01.360 --> 00:10:05.600
it changes the way you see and treat others.

235
00:10:07.480 --> 00:10:10.680
So 1 John chapter four, verses seven and eight,

236
00:10:10.680 --> 00:10:12.520
the apostle John says it very clearly here,

237
00:10:12.520 --> 00:10:14.840
beloved, let us love one another,

238
00:10:14.840 --> 00:10:16.960
for love is from God,

239
00:10:16.960 --> 00:10:19.440
and everyone who loves has been born of God

240
00:10:19.440 --> 00:10:20.920
and knows God.

241
00:10:20.920 --> 00:10:24.680
Anyone who does not love does not know God

242
00:10:24.680 --> 00:10:28.000
because God is love.

243
00:10:28.520 --> 00:10:32.800
So love shows that we truly know the Lord because He is love.

244
00:10:33.880 --> 00:10:36.280
So here, Paul is even more assured though,

245
00:10:36.280 --> 00:10:37.800
he says that he could see that love there,

246
00:10:37.800 --> 00:10:39.520
but there's an even extra layer of assurance

247
00:10:39.520 --> 00:10:43.000
because they have love for all the saints.

248
00:10:43.000 --> 00:10:46.720
You see, anybody in the world can love people

249
00:10:46.720 --> 00:10:49.400
that they would naturally get along with.

250
00:10:49.400 --> 00:10:52.160
They can love their family, they can love their friends,

251
00:10:52.160 --> 00:10:53.960
but it takes a supernatural love

252
00:10:53.960 --> 00:10:56.560
that would draw us towards those

253
00:10:56.560 --> 00:10:59.200
we would naturally want to avoid.

254
00:10:59.200 --> 00:11:01.160
So there's a love for all the saints,

255
00:11:01.160 --> 00:11:05.160
not just the ones I would naturally get along with.

256
00:11:05.160 --> 00:11:07.320
That's evidence of the love of God,

257
00:11:07.320 --> 00:11:11.360
the God who loves sinners that we love all the saints.

258
00:11:12.520 --> 00:11:14.040
So faith and love together.

259
00:11:14.040 --> 00:11:15.960
And it's important before we move on

260
00:11:15.960 --> 00:11:19.680
that we hold these two truths together simultaneously.

261
00:11:20.800 --> 00:11:22.880
And if you hold both of those together,

262
00:11:22.880 --> 00:11:25.960
you might counter then some of the lies you hear

263
00:11:26.000 --> 00:11:27.800
you might notice some of the lies you hear.

264
00:11:27.800 --> 00:11:30.720
So one of them say in relation to faith,

265
00:11:30.720 --> 00:11:31.960
you might hear somebody say it,

266
00:11:31.960 --> 00:11:34.840
I've had this said to me in conversation before,

267
00:11:34.840 --> 00:11:36.960
well, you know, we all believe different things,

268
00:11:36.960 --> 00:11:39.000
different religions of the world all believe different things,

269
00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:40.400
but at the end of the day,

270
00:11:40.400 --> 00:11:43.480
what really matters is how we treat one another.

271
00:11:46.360 --> 00:11:49.240
And I see that the sentiment of love

272
00:11:49.240 --> 00:11:52.240
in what they're saying there, but are they right?

273
00:11:53.240 --> 00:11:58.240
God makes it clear that what we believe really matters.

274
00:11:58.680 --> 00:12:01.040
Like it really matters what your faith in.

275
00:12:01.040 --> 00:12:05.040
Like your eternity is resting on something.

276
00:12:05.040 --> 00:12:07.480
And I hope it is not resting on

277
00:12:07.480 --> 00:12:09.360
how well you treat other people.

278
00:12:09.360 --> 00:12:11.560
I hope my eternity isn't resting in that it isn't.

279
00:12:11.560 --> 00:12:14.440
It's through faith in Jesus that matters.

280
00:12:15.520 --> 00:12:18.480
But also that's not to say that our works do not matter

281
00:12:18.480 --> 00:12:21.120
or that our love for others don't matter.

282
00:12:21.320 --> 00:12:23.560
So on the flip side, you might have someone who says,

283
00:12:23.560 --> 00:12:26.040
you know, that they really feel justified

284
00:12:26.040 --> 00:12:28.440
in treating other people harshly.

285
00:12:29.720 --> 00:12:33.880
Because what really matters is believing the right things.

286
00:12:33.880 --> 00:12:36.680
Like they're looking, they might want to,

287
00:12:36.680 --> 00:12:39.080
they're really boastful in what they believe

288
00:12:39.080 --> 00:12:41.080
and they're just looking to destroy other people

289
00:12:41.080 --> 00:12:43.400
with the arguments that they make towards them.

290
00:12:43.400 --> 00:12:47.560
And there's a really harsh spirit towards other people.

291
00:12:48.560 --> 00:12:52.440
But here we see that knowing God is seen in our love for others

292
00:12:52.440 --> 00:12:56.320
as well as in what we believe about God.

293
00:12:56.320 --> 00:13:00.480
So I don't mean that if you sin, you're definitely not saved.

294
00:13:00.480 --> 00:13:02.560
But if you say, Jesus is my king,

295
00:13:02.560 --> 00:13:05.360
then surely something should be seen of following him.

296
00:13:05.360 --> 00:13:09.240
Something of his love should be coming through in your life.

297
00:13:10.400 --> 00:13:12.400
If that's not the case, it's not saying,

298
00:13:12.400 --> 00:13:13.840
well, you definitely don't know him,

299
00:13:13.840 --> 00:13:17.080
but your grounds for assurance that you know him

300
00:13:17.080 --> 00:13:18.100
are really shaky.

301
00:13:19.640 --> 00:13:21.480
So put your faith in Jesus.

302
00:13:22.600 --> 00:13:26.520
So that's how we know that we know him.

303
00:13:26.520 --> 00:13:28.120
My trusting in Jesus.

304
00:13:28.120 --> 00:13:30.800
And that's evidence in our love for others.

305
00:13:30.800 --> 00:13:33.520
So how do we then grow in the knowledge of God?

306
00:13:33.520 --> 00:13:35.620
This is what Paul's really praying for here.

307
00:13:36.600 --> 00:13:39.560
So we get the answer by looking at the specific ways

308
00:13:39.560 --> 00:13:41.640
that he prays that they might grow

309
00:13:41.640 --> 00:13:42.760
in the knowledge of God.

310
00:13:42.760 --> 00:13:44.560
So let's walk through those together.

311
00:13:44.560 --> 00:13:46.600
So there's a receiving element

312
00:13:46.600 --> 00:13:48.320
and there's a pursuing element.

313
00:13:48.320 --> 00:13:51.000
So let's look at the receiving element first.

314
00:13:51.000 --> 00:13:55.200
So he's praying that they might be,

315
00:13:55.200 --> 00:13:56.320
you see it in verse 17,

316
00:13:56.320 --> 00:13:58.880
that the God of our Lord Jesus Christ,

317
00:13:58.880 --> 00:14:02.760
the Father of glory may give you the spirit of wisdom

318
00:14:02.760 --> 00:14:05.840
and of revelation in the knowledge of him.

319
00:14:05.840 --> 00:14:07.840
So here's how we grow in the knowledge of God

320
00:14:07.840 --> 00:14:11.160
by being given the spirit.

321
00:14:11.160 --> 00:14:13.520
God gives us his spirit.

322
00:14:13.520 --> 00:14:15.640
So you might say, well, hang on a second.

323
00:14:16.640 --> 00:14:17.880
Over the last couple of weeks,

324
00:14:17.880 --> 00:14:22.880
we've seen that everyone who believes in Christ

325
00:14:23.520 --> 00:14:25.280
is sealed with the Holy Spirit.

326
00:14:25.280 --> 00:14:26.260
And that's absolutely true.

327
00:14:26.260 --> 00:14:27.640
You go back in verse 13,

328
00:14:27.640 --> 00:14:31.160
you see that we're given the Holy Spirit when we believe.

329
00:14:31.160 --> 00:14:32.280
That's right.

330
00:14:32.280 --> 00:14:33.960
So what is Paul saying here

331
00:14:34.960 --> 00:14:37.480
that we're given the spirit then after that?

332
00:14:37.480 --> 00:14:39.040
What's going on here?

333
00:14:39.040 --> 00:14:42.480
What he's talking about is knowing the work

334
00:14:42.480 --> 00:14:44.680
of the spirit in increasing measure.

335
00:14:44.720 --> 00:14:45.960
That's what he's been talking about

336
00:14:45.960 --> 00:14:47.800
when he talks about being given the spirit of wisdom

337
00:14:47.800 --> 00:14:50.080
and revelation, knowing the work of the spirit

338
00:14:50.080 --> 00:14:52.760
in increasing measure because you cannot separate

339
00:14:52.760 --> 00:14:54.880
the person of the Holy Spirit

340
00:14:54.880 --> 00:14:58.320
and the work of the Holy Spirit.

341
00:14:58.320 --> 00:15:00.280
So we're knowing his work more.

342
00:15:02.160 --> 00:15:05.240
So in other words, he's praying that the spirit of God

343
00:15:05.240 --> 00:15:09.360
would make more and more of God known to them

344
00:15:09.360 --> 00:15:11.840
as he works in their lives.

345
00:15:11.880 --> 00:15:15.000
So God is personally making himself known to us

346
00:15:15.000 --> 00:15:15.840
by the spirit.

347
00:15:15.840 --> 00:15:19.840
So when we have scripture here in front of us,

348
00:15:19.840 --> 00:15:22.280
for example, God doesn't just give us a book

349
00:15:22.280 --> 00:15:24.440
and then kind of send us off on our own to say,

350
00:15:24.440 --> 00:15:26.400
well, this is what shows,

351
00:15:26.400 --> 00:15:27.880
the Bible shows what I'm like.

352
00:15:27.880 --> 00:15:30.600
It's over to you to figure that out.

353
00:15:30.600 --> 00:15:31.800
Like it's true that this tells us

354
00:15:31.800 --> 00:15:33.440
what God is like truly,

355
00:15:33.440 --> 00:15:37.840
but God personally comes to us in the work of his spirit

356
00:15:37.840 --> 00:15:40.800
and shows us the truth that he tells us about

357
00:15:40.800 --> 00:15:41.680
in his word.

358
00:15:42.040 --> 00:15:43.880
It's his very present and work

359
00:15:43.880 --> 00:15:47.400
that causes us to grow in knowledge.

360
00:15:47.400 --> 00:15:51.200
So we can't understand spiritual truth on our own.

361
00:15:51.200 --> 00:15:54.120
So if you go back to 1 Corinthians in chapter two,

362
00:15:54.120 --> 00:15:55.200
verses six to 16,

363
00:15:55.200 --> 00:15:57.440
I wish we could kind of walk through all of that together

364
00:15:57.440 --> 00:15:59.760
because this deals with this at length really.

365
00:16:01.240 --> 00:16:02.840
There Paul is essentially talking about

366
00:16:02.840 --> 00:16:05.760
how we cannot figure out spiritual truths

367
00:16:05.760 --> 00:16:08.160
by mere natural wisdom.

368
00:16:08.160 --> 00:16:11.200
They must be taught to us by the spirit of God.

369
00:16:11.240 --> 00:16:13.160
Who better to tell us the mind of God

370
00:16:13.160 --> 00:16:16.560
than God himself by his spirit?

371
00:16:16.560 --> 00:16:18.720
So we've got to be taught by the spirit.

372
00:16:18.720 --> 00:16:20.960
They have to be revealed to us by the spirit.

373
00:16:20.960 --> 00:16:23.560
It's like the lights are out

374
00:16:23.560 --> 00:16:26.400
when it comes to just our natural mind, our natural man.

375
00:16:26.400 --> 00:16:29.040
And they have to be turned on for us to see these truths.

376
00:16:29.040 --> 00:16:32.160
How are they turned on by the work of the spirit?

377
00:16:32.160 --> 00:16:34.000
And so that's what we see here.

378
00:16:34.000 --> 00:16:36.240
So to be given the spirit is to

379
00:16:36.240 --> 00:16:38.880
have the eyes of our hearts enlightened.

380
00:16:38.880 --> 00:16:41.120
Do you see that in verse 18?

381
00:16:41.160 --> 00:16:44.320
Having the eyes of your hearts enlightened

382
00:16:44.320 --> 00:16:45.840
that you may know.

383
00:16:45.840 --> 00:16:46.680
So Paul's there.

384
00:16:46.680 --> 00:16:47.760
What does that mean?

385
00:16:47.760 --> 00:16:50.000
To have the eyes of our hearts enlightened.

386
00:16:50.000 --> 00:16:53.600
What a strange phrase to mix eyes and hearts together.

387
00:16:53.600 --> 00:16:54.720
What's going on here?

388
00:16:54.720 --> 00:16:56.360
Well, let's just separate those out.

389
00:16:56.360 --> 00:16:57.320
So biblically speaking,

390
00:16:57.320 --> 00:17:00.080
the heart is the center of your being,

391
00:17:00.080 --> 00:17:02.240
the center of who you are.

392
00:17:02.240 --> 00:17:06.000
It includes both your mind and your emotions.

393
00:17:06.920 --> 00:17:08.880
Okay, so take that.

394
00:17:08.880 --> 00:17:12.720
Then we say then to have the eyes of your heart enlightened

395
00:17:12.720 --> 00:17:17.720
is to see something both truly and experientially.

396
00:17:17.720 --> 00:17:20.360
Right, so if the heart involves both the mind and the emotions

397
00:17:20.360 --> 00:17:22.720
to have the eyes of our hearts enlightened

398
00:17:22.720 --> 00:17:25.760
is to see something, to know something truly

399
00:17:25.760 --> 00:17:26.960
and experientially.

400
00:17:29.080 --> 00:17:30.560
There's no better way to illustrate this

401
00:17:30.560 --> 00:17:31.880
than biscuits and gravy.

402
00:17:34.440 --> 00:17:36.280
No, I'm sure there's much better ways.

403
00:17:37.240 --> 00:17:40.080
I was, so when I was in England,

404
00:17:40.080 --> 00:17:41.640
people said often to me like,

405
00:17:41.640 --> 00:17:44.000
hey, what kind of food do you miss back in the States?

406
00:17:44.000 --> 00:17:46.520
And first thing that we call this kind of in my mind

407
00:17:46.520 --> 00:17:49.320
is biscuits, we'll start there.

408
00:17:49.320 --> 00:17:51.320
And I said, you know, the best way to have biscuits

409
00:17:51.320 --> 00:17:52.600
is with gravy.

410
00:17:52.600 --> 00:17:55.800
And you can imagine your kind of average Brit hearing that.

411
00:17:55.800 --> 00:17:57.600
First of all, biscuits is a cookie.

412
00:17:57.600 --> 00:17:59.960
And then gravy is a kind of brown gravy

413
00:17:59.960 --> 00:18:02.040
that you might put on turkey or something.

414
00:18:02.040 --> 00:18:03.960
And they said to have biscuits and gravy.

415
00:18:03.960 --> 00:18:05.560
But generally speaking, most people know,

416
00:18:05.640 --> 00:18:06.640
apart from like children,

417
00:18:06.640 --> 00:18:08.640
that you're talking about something different.

418
00:18:08.640 --> 00:18:09.640
And so if you're over there

419
00:18:09.640 --> 00:18:11.240
and you're explaining biscuits and gravy,

420
00:18:11.240 --> 00:18:12.480
how would you explain it to somebody?

421
00:18:12.480 --> 00:18:15.600
What is a biscuit to somebody who's never seen one before

422
00:18:15.600 --> 00:18:17.040
or tasted one before?

423
00:18:17.960 --> 00:18:20.960
I mean, I kind of thought of, it's kind of like a scone,

424
00:18:20.960 --> 00:18:23.440
but it's not sweet and it's not exactly like a scone.

425
00:18:23.440 --> 00:18:25.080
And you try to explain it.

426
00:18:25.080 --> 00:18:27.000
And gravy, well, it's like that,

427
00:18:27.000 --> 00:18:28.160
but it's kind of like white gravy,

428
00:18:28.160 --> 00:18:30.280
but it's got sausage and it's got a bit of,

429
00:18:30.280 --> 00:18:33.680
it still doesn't do justice to what you're trying to say.

430
00:18:33.720 --> 00:18:35.600
But we had some visitors come to see us

431
00:18:35.600 --> 00:18:38.080
a couple months ago from the UK,

432
00:18:38.080 --> 00:18:41.120
and I was finally able to truly explain it.

433
00:18:41.120 --> 00:18:43.000
So I was like, you've got to have biscuits and gravy

434
00:18:43.000 --> 00:18:44.000
while you're here.

435
00:18:44.000 --> 00:18:45.920
And the best way for me to, I can explain it to you,

436
00:18:45.920 --> 00:18:47.480
but the best way for you to know what it is

437
00:18:47.480 --> 00:18:50.960
is to just taste it, to taste it.

438
00:18:50.960 --> 00:18:53.480
All right, so there's a knowledge part of it

439
00:18:53.480 --> 00:18:55.960
and there's an experience part of it.

440
00:18:55.960 --> 00:18:58.440
All right, so to have the eyes of your heart enlightened

441
00:18:58.440 --> 00:19:02.440
is to know God truly, like these facts about Him,

442
00:19:02.480 --> 00:19:06.920
but also experientially to be drawn into the reality

443
00:19:06.920 --> 00:19:08.920
of what that truth is saying.

444
00:19:08.920 --> 00:19:12.600
It is tasting and seeing that the Lord is good.

445
00:19:12.600 --> 00:19:15.480
So knowing God involves our understanding, yes,

446
00:19:15.480 --> 00:19:18.360
but it also involves our affections.

447
00:19:18.360 --> 00:19:22.440
It is rational and it is also emotional.

448
00:19:22.440 --> 00:19:25.920
There is light and there is heat.

449
00:19:28.360 --> 00:19:30.200
So it's something that we receive,

450
00:19:30.200 --> 00:19:32.160
but it's also something we pursue.

451
00:19:32.200 --> 00:19:34.840
So God is the one who gives us the knowledge of Him.

452
00:19:34.840 --> 00:19:37.920
He's the one who comes to us in the work of His Spirit.

453
00:19:37.920 --> 00:19:40.640
But we're called to pursue this knowledge too.

454
00:19:40.640 --> 00:19:42.000
You see this all the way throughout Scripture.

455
00:19:42.000 --> 00:19:45.480
So Hosea chapter six, verse three, wonderful verse,

456
00:19:45.480 --> 00:19:48.280
simple verse, it says, let us know,

457
00:19:48.280 --> 00:19:51.920
let us pursue the knowledge of the Lord.

458
00:19:51.920 --> 00:19:54.440
It's the same kind of knowledge being spoken of here.

459
00:19:54.440 --> 00:19:56.600
You see this right the way throughout the Psalms,

460
00:19:56.600 --> 00:19:57.760
I mean you can just name Psalm after Psalm,

461
00:19:57.760 --> 00:20:00.520
but Psalm 27 says this,

462
00:20:00.520 --> 00:20:02.320
one thing have I asked the Lord

463
00:20:02.320 --> 00:20:04.520
and that will I seek after,

464
00:20:04.520 --> 00:20:06.840
that I may dwell in the house of the Lord

465
00:20:06.840 --> 00:20:10.680
all the days of my life to gaze upon the beauty of the Lord

466
00:20:10.680 --> 00:20:12.960
and to inquire in His temple.

467
00:20:12.960 --> 00:20:15.660
You have said, seek my face.

468
00:20:15.660 --> 00:20:20.560
My heart says to you, your face, oh Lord, do I seek?

469
00:20:20.560 --> 00:20:23.800
He's seeking after the knowledge of God in prayer,

470
00:20:23.800 --> 00:20:25.660
gazing upon His beauty.

471
00:20:26.700 --> 00:20:29.040
You see this in Philippians chapter three in verse eight

472
00:20:29.080 --> 00:20:32.640
and Paul is giving his testimony, telling his story

473
00:20:32.640 --> 00:20:36.080
and he says this, he says, I count everything as loss

474
00:20:36.080 --> 00:20:41.080
compared to the surpassing worth of knowing Christ.

475
00:20:42.240 --> 00:20:45.120
And then he says, for his sake I've suffered the loss

476
00:20:45.120 --> 00:20:46.800
of all things and count them as rubbish

477
00:20:46.800 --> 00:20:49.720
in order that I may gain Christ.

478
00:20:49.720 --> 00:20:51.880
He goes on to talk about continuing

479
00:20:51.880 --> 00:20:54.320
in that pursuit of the Lord.

480
00:20:54.320 --> 00:20:58.240
Fact is the greatest pursuit in life is the pursuit of God.

481
00:20:58.320 --> 00:21:01.480
It's what we're called to devote our lives to really.

482
00:21:02.560 --> 00:21:04.960
So where do we see that here in the text?

483
00:21:04.960 --> 00:21:06.800
Well it's kind of implicit here.

484
00:21:08.680 --> 00:21:09.520
Let's see it this way.

485
00:21:09.520 --> 00:21:12.580
Paul is writing about these specific truths

486
00:21:12.580 --> 00:21:14.920
that are revealed by the spirit

487
00:21:14.920 --> 00:21:19.480
and he's also praying for their knowledge of the Lord.

488
00:21:20.640 --> 00:21:23.080
So to say that knowledge of the Lord

489
00:21:23.080 --> 00:21:25.440
is something that is given,

490
00:21:25.440 --> 00:21:27.560
isn't to say we just passively sit back

491
00:21:27.600 --> 00:21:31.720
and kind of wait for it to mystically happen to us.

492
00:21:31.720 --> 00:21:34.840
Paul wants them to know some things about the Lord as well

493
00:21:34.840 --> 00:21:36.600
and he's praying as well.

494
00:21:36.600 --> 00:21:38.480
So he's involved in this whole process of them

495
00:21:38.480 --> 00:21:40.120
knowing the Lord in his prayer.

496
00:21:41.040 --> 00:21:43.000
So what does the pursuit look like for us?

497
00:21:43.000 --> 00:21:47.680
It looks like us being driven to what is written

498
00:21:47.680 --> 00:21:50.560
in his word that we may know more about him.

499
00:21:50.560 --> 00:21:53.400
It's here that we find out about his attributes

500
00:21:53.400 --> 00:21:54.240
and his ways.

501
00:21:54.280 --> 00:21:57.880
It is here that we see his glory displayed.

502
00:21:57.880 --> 00:21:59.680
So this is what pursuit of God looks like,

503
00:21:59.680 --> 00:22:03.360
wanting to know him in his word.

504
00:22:03.360 --> 00:22:05.800
It also looks like prayer.

505
00:22:05.800 --> 00:22:07.120
As we see more about him,

506
00:22:07.120 --> 00:22:09.640
it leads us to praise and prayer

507
00:22:09.640 --> 00:22:12.520
like we see the apostle Paul demonstrating here.

508
00:22:12.520 --> 00:22:15.400
It's coming to this God himself.

509
00:22:15.400 --> 00:22:18.160
It's a personal relationship remember.

510
00:22:18.160 --> 00:22:21.680
And notice as well that he's writing to fellow believers.

511
00:22:21.720 --> 00:22:24.640
This letter is being read in the life of a church.

512
00:22:24.640 --> 00:22:27.260
We pursue the Lord together.

513
00:22:28.320 --> 00:22:32.040
This involves our kind of personal quiet time with the Lord

514
00:22:32.040 --> 00:22:34.320
but it's also a collective pursuit.

515
00:22:34.320 --> 00:22:38.100
We need to hear one another speaking the truth of God

516
00:22:38.100 --> 00:22:39.520
to each other.

517
00:22:39.520 --> 00:22:41.200
We need to pray for one another.

518
00:22:41.200 --> 00:22:43.960
So a church that is centered on the word of God

519
00:22:43.960 --> 00:22:45.480
and when it says about him in a church

520
00:22:45.480 --> 00:22:47.280
that is praying for one another

521
00:22:47.280 --> 00:22:48.760
and seeking after God in that way

522
00:22:48.760 --> 00:22:51.000
is a church that will be growing

523
00:22:51.000 --> 00:22:54.080
in the knowledge of the Lord together.

524
00:22:54.920 --> 00:22:57.920
So we don't do these things out of a sense of guilt.

525
00:22:57.920 --> 00:22:59.720
Like I've got to read my Bible.

526
00:22:59.720 --> 00:23:02.960
I haven't prayed for a while so I really should pray.

527
00:23:02.960 --> 00:23:06.640
It's wanting to know him that drives us.

528
00:23:06.640 --> 00:23:08.360
It's the pursuit of God.

529
00:23:09.520 --> 00:23:11.520
So what might this look like practically?

530
00:23:11.520 --> 00:23:13.840
Well Paul gives us then three examples

531
00:23:13.840 --> 00:23:15.160
of what this sort of looks like.

532
00:23:15.160 --> 00:23:17.480
All right so in practice like what does it look like

533
00:23:17.480 --> 00:23:20.200
to be pursuing the knowledge of God

534
00:23:20.200 --> 00:23:24.760
to have the eyes of our hearts enlightened by the spirit.

535
00:23:24.760 --> 00:23:27.520
So the three things that Paul says we'll know

536
00:23:27.520 --> 00:23:30.680
as the spirit enlightens the eyes of our hearts

537
00:23:30.680 --> 00:23:33.360
as he draws us further into the knowledge of God.

538
00:23:34.200 --> 00:23:37.720
First of all he talks about the hope of his calling.

539
00:23:37.720 --> 00:23:39.400
There in verse 18,

540
00:23:39.400 --> 00:23:40.960
from the eyes of our hearts are enlightened

541
00:23:40.960 --> 00:23:44.800
we know what is the hope to which he has called you.

542
00:23:44.800 --> 00:23:46.960
Literally the hope of his calling.

543
00:23:46.960 --> 00:23:48.960
So what is his calling?

544
00:23:48.960 --> 00:23:51.040
In some ways when he talks about the calling here

545
00:23:51.040 --> 00:23:54.400
it's a one word summary of everything he was praising God

546
00:23:54.400 --> 00:23:58.040
for that we've looked at the past couple weeks together.

547
00:23:58.040 --> 00:24:02.560
He's praising God or he's talking about us knowing

548
00:24:02.560 --> 00:24:06.320
the calling or us knowing the initiative

549
00:24:06.320 --> 00:24:09.760
that God took to make us his own.

550
00:24:09.760 --> 00:24:11.120
That's his calling.

551
00:24:11.120 --> 00:24:14.560
It's when you became a Christian if you know the Lord.

552
00:24:14.560 --> 00:24:16.920
So if you're a true believer it's because God

553
00:24:17.080 --> 00:24:18.680
called you to himself.

554
00:24:20.360 --> 00:24:21.640
Do we call upon the Lord?

555
00:24:21.640 --> 00:24:25.160
Yes whoever calls upon the name of the Lord will be saved.

556
00:24:25.160 --> 00:24:30.160
But we call upon the Lord because he calls us.

557
00:24:30.320 --> 00:24:32.600
And his calling is part of an unbroken chain

558
00:24:32.600 --> 00:24:34.920
that begins before the foundation of the world.

559
00:24:34.920 --> 00:24:36.160
You see that in Ephesians one

560
00:24:36.160 --> 00:24:38.480
but there's a great verse Romans 8 30

561
00:24:38.480 --> 00:24:39.960
that summarizes this.

562
00:24:39.960 --> 00:24:41.400
You see this sort of unbroken chain

563
00:24:41.400 --> 00:24:42.360
in what Paul writes there.

564
00:24:42.360 --> 00:24:46.040
He says, and those whom he predestined,

565
00:24:46.080 --> 00:24:48.000
he also called.

566
00:24:48.000 --> 00:24:51.840
And those whom he called, he also justified.

567
00:24:51.840 --> 00:24:56.200
And those whom he justified, he also glorified.

568
00:24:56.200 --> 00:25:00.960
Right, so there's a hope to be had in his calling.

569
00:25:00.960 --> 00:25:04.320
Right, so the certainty of his effectual call

570
00:25:04.320 --> 00:25:06.080
gives us hope.

571
00:25:06.080 --> 00:25:07.480
So the hope being spoken of here

572
00:25:07.480 --> 00:25:09.360
isn't it kind of like an uncertain wish?

573
00:25:09.360 --> 00:25:12.840
Like I really hope we have some good weather here next week.

574
00:25:12.840 --> 00:25:15.720
It's not that, it's a definite assurance.

575
00:25:15.720 --> 00:25:18.320
I can know that I belong to the Lord

576
00:25:18.320 --> 00:25:20.040
and will one day be with him

577
00:25:20.040 --> 00:25:23.200
because he called me.

578
00:25:23.200 --> 00:25:24.280
He made me his own.

579
00:25:25.920 --> 00:25:28.440
Okay, so the spirit of God assures our hearts

580
00:25:28.440 --> 00:25:32.080
by opening our eyes to see the certainty

581
00:25:32.080 --> 00:25:35.080
of the fact that God has called us.

582
00:25:36.080 --> 00:25:37.400
But also what's another thing

583
00:25:37.400 --> 00:25:39.440
that the spirit opens our eyes to?

584
00:25:39.440 --> 00:25:41.480
The glory of his inheritance.

585
00:25:42.720 --> 00:25:44.440
So the hope to which he's called you.

586
00:25:44.440 --> 00:25:46.840
And then also in verse 18, there at the end,

587
00:25:46.840 --> 00:25:50.400
what are the riches of his glorious inheritance

588
00:25:50.400 --> 00:25:52.600
in the saints?

589
00:25:53.760 --> 00:25:57.760
So notice there that he isn't talking about our inheritance.

590
00:25:58.560 --> 00:25:59.600
You might read it in that way.

591
00:25:59.600 --> 00:26:02.240
He's talking about the inheritance that is coming to us.

592
00:26:02.240 --> 00:26:04.200
Like he spoke about that before

593
00:26:04.200 --> 00:26:06.280
and we looked at that before.

594
00:26:06.280 --> 00:26:08.800
He's talking about God's inheritance.

595
00:26:08.800 --> 00:26:10.480
So he wants us to know God's inheritance.

596
00:26:10.480 --> 00:26:12.320
Well, what is that?

597
00:26:12.320 --> 00:26:13.360
What does he want us to know here?

598
00:26:13.360 --> 00:26:15.080
And we might think well,

599
00:26:15.080 --> 00:26:18.480
what riches could God possibly inherit?

600
00:26:18.480 --> 00:26:21.240
I mean think of, I don't know, Elon Musk.

601
00:26:21.240 --> 00:26:24.960
Right, say you strike up a friendship with your buddy Elon

602
00:26:24.960 --> 00:26:28.800
and it's come time for his birthday

603
00:26:28.800 --> 00:26:30.840
and you wanna really buy him something.

604
00:26:30.840 --> 00:26:34.000
But what can you buy the richest man in the world

605
00:26:34.000 --> 00:26:35.160
that he really needs?

606
00:26:35.160 --> 00:26:40.160
Like, what is it that he would really treasure and say,

607
00:26:40.480 --> 00:26:41.720
I've always wanted this.

608
00:26:41.720 --> 00:26:42.920
I wasn't able to get this.

609
00:26:42.920 --> 00:26:45.520
I've finally able to have this.

610
00:26:45.520 --> 00:26:47.920
Be a really hard person to buy for.

611
00:26:47.920 --> 00:26:49.640
Somebody who has everything.

612
00:26:50.760 --> 00:26:51.800
Over the past couple of weeks,

613
00:26:51.800 --> 00:26:54.080
we've seen God's absolute sovereignty.

614
00:26:54.080 --> 00:26:55.600
Right, he's over everything.

615
00:26:55.600 --> 00:26:58.440
He can have whatever he wants.

616
00:26:58.440 --> 00:27:00.640
And yet we're told here that there is a treasure

617
00:27:00.640 --> 00:27:03.120
that he just can't wait to receive.

618
00:27:03.120 --> 00:27:06.960
There are some riches that he has his eyes on.

619
00:27:06.960 --> 00:27:08.440
What are these riches?

620
00:27:08.440 --> 00:27:10.720
What is his inheritance?

621
00:27:10.720 --> 00:27:11.660
Is this wonderful?

622
00:27:12.660 --> 00:27:13.980
It's us.

623
00:27:13.980 --> 00:27:17.540
His inheritance is in the saints.

624
00:27:17.540 --> 00:27:19.220
We are the ones he is waiting on.

625
00:27:19.220 --> 00:27:20.940
He is looking forward to the day

626
00:27:20.940 --> 00:27:23.900
when he gathers the people he has made perfect

627
00:27:23.900 --> 00:27:26.340
through Christ.

628
00:27:26.340 --> 00:27:29.620
We are his treasured inheritance.

629
00:27:29.620 --> 00:27:31.620
I mean that might make you uncomfortable

630
00:27:31.620 --> 00:27:33.700
to think of God thinking of you in that way

631
00:27:33.700 --> 00:27:36.180
but he absolutely does.

632
00:27:36.180 --> 00:27:37.700
Either you look back in the Old Testament,

633
00:27:37.700 --> 00:27:39.500
Zechariah chapter three verse 17,

634
00:27:39.500 --> 00:27:42.100
it speaks about the Lord rejoicing

635
00:27:42.100 --> 00:27:45.180
over his people with gladness.

636
00:27:45.180 --> 00:27:47.340
That is how the Lord looks upon us.

637
00:27:47.340 --> 00:27:52.100
Christian, God absolutely treasures you.

638
00:27:52.100 --> 00:27:53.660
You are treasured.

639
00:27:53.660 --> 00:27:57.020
You are more loved than you can possibly imagine.

640
00:27:57.020 --> 00:27:59.980
And one of the things that God wants to do

641
00:27:59.980 --> 00:28:02.340
in your life through his spirit

642
00:28:03.380 --> 00:28:05.300
is to draw you into that reality,

643
00:28:05.340 --> 00:28:10.260
to experience more of his great love for you.

644
00:28:10.260 --> 00:28:13.460
To not just know it intellectually in your mind

645
00:28:13.460 --> 00:28:14.980
but to know it in your heart of hearts

646
00:28:14.980 --> 00:28:16.540
that you are loved by God.

647
00:28:17.940 --> 00:28:20.740
It's been compared before to like a father

648
00:28:20.740 --> 00:28:22.740
walking down the road with his daughter

649
00:28:22.740 --> 00:28:24.060
and as they're walking down the road

650
00:28:24.060 --> 00:28:26.220
he says to her, I love you.

651
00:28:27.100 --> 00:28:29.780
And the daughter believes what he says

652
00:28:29.780 --> 00:28:32.420
but then a moment later he says, I really love you.

653
00:28:32.420 --> 00:28:35.100
And he picks up his daughter and he swings her around

654
00:28:35.100 --> 00:28:36.900
and their eyed eyes and he swings around.

655
00:28:36.900 --> 00:28:39.900
He draws her in close and gives her this big hug.

656
00:28:40.900 --> 00:28:44.180
That's the work of the spirit being spoken of here.

657
00:28:44.180 --> 00:28:46.900
So God is making it known that he loves us.

658
00:28:46.900 --> 00:28:49.060
We are in his inheritance and the spirit

659
00:28:49.060 --> 00:28:51.280
draws us into that reality.

660
00:28:53.020 --> 00:28:56.700
He drives home the truth that we are loved by God.

661
00:28:58.180 --> 00:29:00.340
But also thirdly see this.

662
00:29:00.340 --> 00:29:02.060
We know the hope of his calling,

663
00:29:02.060 --> 00:29:03.100
that we are in his inheritance.

664
00:29:03.100 --> 00:29:05.140
We also know the power of his might.

665
00:29:06.180 --> 00:29:08.540
Verses 19 to 23.

666
00:29:08.540 --> 00:29:11.060
The apostle Paul is praying that they might know

667
00:29:11.060 --> 00:29:13.540
God's great power.

668
00:29:13.540 --> 00:29:16.020
What is the immeasurable greatness of his power

669
00:29:16.020 --> 00:29:18.860
towards us who believe according to the working

670
00:29:18.860 --> 00:29:21.840
of his great might?

671
00:29:22.620 --> 00:29:25.500
A couple of weeks ago I watched a video

672
00:29:25.500 --> 00:29:27.940
of the eruption of Mount St. Helens.

673
00:29:27.940 --> 00:29:30.860
It was really unbelievable to watch it.

674
00:29:30.860 --> 00:29:33.020
It was unreal just seeing this mountain

675
00:29:33.060 --> 00:29:35.020
just begin to crumble.

676
00:29:35.020 --> 00:29:38.260
You know it was considered to be the most powerful

677
00:29:38.260 --> 00:29:41.660
volcanic eruption in US history.

678
00:29:41.660 --> 00:29:46.700
The blast force equivalent was that of 10 to 50 megatons

679
00:29:46.700 --> 00:29:48.220
of TNT.

680
00:29:49.060 --> 00:29:51.660
It demolished the northern side of the volcano

681
00:29:51.660 --> 00:29:54.380
and sent a massive ash cloud up into the air

682
00:29:54.380 --> 00:29:57.280
over 80,000 feet.

683
00:29:57.280 --> 00:29:58.300
Hard to imagine.

684
00:29:59.300 --> 00:30:03.620
In a matter of minutes over 230 square miles

685
00:30:03.620 --> 00:30:06.420
were destroyed and it permanently altered

686
00:30:06.420 --> 00:30:07.340
the mountain's shape.

687
00:30:07.340 --> 00:30:11.660
It reduced its height by at least 1,300 feet.

688
00:30:12.820 --> 00:30:14.540
So powerful.

689
00:30:14.540 --> 00:30:16.220
And yet here's the thing about that blast.

690
00:30:16.220 --> 00:30:19.660
Its power was measurable.

691
00:30:19.660 --> 00:30:20.940
We can give the statistics,

692
00:30:20.940 --> 00:30:22.100
we can talk through the numbers.

693
00:30:22.100 --> 00:30:23.260
It's measurable.

694
00:30:23.260 --> 00:30:26.460
But notice how God's power is described in verse 19.

695
00:30:26.580 --> 00:30:28.260
It's immeasurable.

696
00:30:30.100 --> 00:30:31.580
It's beyond knowing.

697
00:30:31.580 --> 00:30:32.940
His power is limitless.

698
00:30:32.940 --> 00:30:37.100
He's the creator and sustainer of all things.

699
00:30:37.100 --> 00:30:41.980
And so his power surpasses every earthly power.

700
00:30:41.980 --> 00:30:44.620
No matter Jeremiah said,

701
00:30:44.620 --> 00:30:47.140
Lord God it is you who has made the heavens

702
00:30:47.140 --> 00:30:48.700
and the earth by your great power

703
00:30:48.700 --> 00:30:50.700
and by your outstretched arm.

704
00:30:50.700 --> 00:30:53.540
Nothing is too hard for you.

705
00:30:54.500 --> 00:30:57.820
And that power is displayed in creation.

706
00:30:57.820 --> 00:30:59.780
But there's a particular demonstration of power

707
00:30:59.780 --> 00:31:02.260
that Paul wants us to see here.

708
00:31:02.260 --> 00:31:05.860
It's the power that he has shown in Christ.

709
00:31:05.860 --> 00:31:09.340
Notice verse 19, it speaks of the working of his great might

710
00:31:09.340 --> 00:31:13.020
that he worked in Christ when?

711
00:31:13.020 --> 00:31:14.380
When he raised him from the dead

712
00:31:14.380 --> 00:31:18.340
and seated him at his right hand in the heavenly places.

713
00:31:18.340 --> 00:31:21.660
So God's power is demonstrated in Christ.

714
00:31:21.660 --> 00:31:24.740
It's demonstrated in his resurrection.

715
00:31:24.740 --> 00:31:27.740
So it was God's power that reached into the tomb

716
00:31:27.740 --> 00:31:31.420
and raised Jesus' lifeless body from the dead

717
00:31:32.260 --> 00:31:34.100
to live forevermore.

718
00:31:35.660 --> 00:31:37.460
But it doesn't stop there.

719
00:31:37.460 --> 00:31:40.260
You see God's power when Jesus is raised

720
00:31:40.260 --> 00:31:42.260
to his heavenly throne.

721
00:31:42.260 --> 00:31:44.180
When it speaks about this, about his ascension here,

722
00:31:44.180 --> 00:31:46.220
it's not so much about a place

723
00:31:46.220 --> 00:31:49.940
so much as it is a position of power and authority

724
00:31:49.940 --> 00:31:52.860
because it's here in verse 21 we see

725
00:31:52.860 --> 00:31:56.500
that he reigns far above all rule and authority

726
00:31:56.500 --> 00:32:00.100
and power and dominion and over every name that is named

727
00:32:00.100 --> 00:32:04.020
not only in this age but also in the one to come.

728
00:32:04.020 --> 00:32:06.580
So maybe I don't know, imagine in your mind's eye

729
00:32:06.580 --> 00:32:08.940
if you can a hierarchy of all the powers

730
00:32:08.940 --> 00:32:10.580
in the world that have ever been.

731
00:32:10.580 --> 00:32:14.740
Maybe the greatest rulers, both famous and infamous

732
00:32:14.740 --> 00:32:18.500
and all the military might that goes behind that

733
00:32:18.540 --> 00:32:19.660
stack them up.

734
00:32:20.660 --> 00:32:23.260
And maybe above and beyond that the greatest powers

735
00:32:23.260 --> 00:32:26.420
in the natural world, in the universe.

736
00:32:26.420 --> 00:32:29.140
And then maybe think about all the spiritual powers

737
00:32:29.140 --> 00:32:31.180
that you could possibly imagine.

738
00:32:31.180 --> 00:32:33.140
And when we read that Jesus ascends

739
00:32:33.140 --> 00:32:36.980
to his heavenly throne, he's being raised above

740
00:32:36.980 --> 00:32:41.980
all power, all power that exists.

741
00:32:44.460 --> 00:32:46.500
His power will never be exceeded.

742
00:32:46.540 --> 00:32:49.540
He reigns today from the highest seat of authority

743
00:32:49.540 --> 00:32:52.080
and he will never be dethroned.

744
00:32:53.340 --> 00:32:57.540
One day the king who reigns in power

745
00:32:57.540 --> 00:33:00.300
will bring evil to its final end

746
00:33:00.300 --> 00:33:04.300
and every tongue will confess that he is Lord.

747
00:33:05.820 --> 00:33:10.660
But notice also in verses 22 and 23 as we finish

748
00:33:10.660 --> 00:33:13.420
that Jesus, this Jesus who's writing in power,

749
00:33:13.420 --> 00:33:16.140
this power that we experience in him

750
00:33:16.140 --> 00:33:18.540
is reigning over his church.

751
00:33:18.540 --> 00:33:19.940
He's the head of the church.

752
00:33:19.940 --> 00:33:22.460
What describes his authority, not just over creation

753
00:33:22.460 --> 00:33:25.580
but the church, but it also shows that we are

754
00:33:28.620 --> 00:33:33.620
inextricably and organically linked with him.

755
00:33:34.140 --> 00:33:37.380
Say he's our head and we are his body.

756
00:33:37.380 --> 00:33:39.780
Right, just like a head is linked to a body.

757
00:33:40.700 --> 00:33:43.300
So we are linked to him.

758
00:33:43.300 --> 00:33:45.820
And his glory fills the church

759
00:33:45.820 --> 00:33:49.580
as we are directed and enabled

760
00:33:49.580 --> 00:33:53.180
by the power of his risen life.

761
00:33:53.180 --> 00:33:56.860
Right, so this God raises Jesus from the dead,

762
00:33:56.860 --> 00:33:58.900
seats him on his heavenly throne

763
00:33:58.900 --> 00:34:00.780
and we are his body in the world

764
00:34:00.780 --> 00:34:03.900
and we are empowered and enabled to live for his glory

765
00:34:03.900 --> 00:34:06.740
by the power of his risen life.

766
00:34:06.740 --> 00:34:11.740
This is the power that the spirit makes known in us.

767
00:34:13.860 --> 00:34:17.100
So think of his resurrection.

768
00:34:17.100 --> 00:34:19.700
We can't defeat death.

769
00:34:19.700 --> 00:34:22.820
But we've seen God's power can defeat it.

770
00:34:22.820 --> 00:34:26.100
And so this same God who raised Jesus from the dead

771
00:34:26.100 --> 00:34:29.740
in him and by his spirit reaches down

772
00:34:29.740 --> 00:34:32.380
to people who are dead in their sins

773
00:34:32.380 --> 00:34:35.420
and gives them new life in Jesus

774
00:34:35.420 --> 00:34:36.600
by the power of his spirit.

775
00:34:36.600 --> 00:34:39.760
He can raise us from the dead and make us new.

776
00:34:40.760 --> 00:34:44.160
Think about his ascension

777
00:34:44.160 --> 00:34:46.800
and how one day he's gonna bring all evil to an end

778
00:34:46.800 --> 00:34:49.960
and he's gonna be recognized as Lord.

779
00:34:49.960 --> 00:34:54.680
We cannot defeat evil by our power, no way.

780
00:34:54.680 --> 00:34:55.640
But God can.

781
00:34:56.920 --> 00:35:01.080
And the same God who raised Jesus to his heavenly throne

782
00:35:01.080 --> 00:35:05.240
enables us by his spirit to say no to sin

783
00:35:05.240 --> 00:35:07.560
and to say yes to righteousness.

784
00:35:07.760 --> 00:35:10.600
This same God, Philippians chapter two verse 13 says

785
00:35:10.600 --> 00:35:14.440
is at work in you, both to desire and to do

786
00:35:14.440 --> 00:35:17.600
that which is pleasing to him.

787
00:35:17.600 --> 00:35:19.000
So think of it.

788
00:35:19.000 --> 00:35:24.000
The God who reigns in power over all things

789
00:35:24.560 --> 00:35:25.760
is at work in you.

790
00:35:27.880 --> 00:35:29.400
And it's only the spirit of God

791
00:35:30.560 --> 00:35:32.640
that can cause you to know that power,

792
00:35:32.640 --> 00:35:35.000
not just here in your head but in your heart

793
00:35:35.040 --> 00:35:37.480
and to live according to that power.

794
00:35:38.520 --> 00:35:40.920
So ask again what I asked at the start.

795
00:35:40.920 --> 00:35:41.920
Do you know him?

796
00:35:43.880 --> 00:35:45.400
Do you want to know him more?

797
00:35:46.400 --> 00:35:49.240
Do you want to want to know him more?

798
00:35:49.240 --> 00:35:52.160
I know I do and I pray you do as well.

799
00:35:52.160 --> 00:35:55.000
So may God by the power of his spirit

800
00:35:55.000 --> 00:35:59.160
open the eyes of our hearts that we may know him.

801
00:35:59.160 --> 00:36:02.960
We might see and savor his calling, his love

802
00:36:02.960 --> 00:36:04.800
and live according to his power.

803
00:36:05.000 --> 00:36:07.440
So let's pray together.

